TY  - JOUR
AU  - Vives, Xavier
T1  - Strategic Complementarity, Fragility, and Regulation
PY  - 2014
Y1  - 2014/12/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhu064
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 27
IS  - 12
SP  - 3547
EP  - 3592
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Fragility is affected by how the balance sheet composition of financial intermediaries, the precision of information signals, and market stress parameters all influence the extent of strategic complementarity among investors' strategies. A solvency and a liquidity ratio are required to control the likelihood of insolvency and illiquidity. The solvency requirement must be strengthened in the face of increased competition, whereas the liquidity requirement must be strengthened under more conservative fund managers and higher penalties for fire sales. Greater disclosure may aggravate fragility and require an increase in the liquidity ratio, so regulators should establish prudential and disclosure policies in tandem.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhu064
ER  - 



