AB  - In “Managerial Incentives and the Role of Advisors in the Continuous-Time Agency Model” by Keiichi Hori and Hiroshi Osano (v. 26 n. 10 pp. 2620–2647), there is an error in the proof of Lemma A1 in the Appendix. This note shows how to correct it by imposing the restriction on the upper bound of the principal's effort. All the conclusions of the paper remain valid.Lemma A1:The solutions to (A3) exist and are unique and continuous in initial conditionsF(W)andF′(W). In addition, if1+αa¯P≤μ, wherea¯Pis the largest value ofaP∈AP, F(W)is strictly concave on [R, WI].
